Iterate enum values via ipairs unconditionally.

Upstream lgi (PR #352) gates this on GLib.check_version(2, 87, 0), but in
nixpkgs glib is 2.86 with the new table-format enum values backported via
glib-2.86.0.patch — so the version check would lie and route to the
broken fromarray() path. Using ipairs unconditionally works because
nixpkgs's glib already provides values as a Lua table.

Applies on top of nixpkgs's lgi glib-2.86.0.patch (which changes
TypeClass.ref -> .get and drops :unref()).

--- a/lgi/ffi.lua
+++ b/lgi/ffi.lua
@@ -82,8 +82,7 @@
    local type_class = GObject.TypeClass.get(gtype)
    local enum_class = core.record.cast(
       type_class, is_flags and GObject.FlagsClass or GObject.EnumClass)
-   for i = 0, enum_class.n_values - 1 do
-      local val = core.record.fromarray(enum_class.values, i)
+   for _, val in ipairs(enum_class.values) do
       enum_component[core.upcase(val.value_nick):gsub('%-', '_')] = val.value
    end
    return enum_component
